        {{/cone}}
        {{#pyramid}}


                Suppose a pyramid of height {{height}} meters had a square base of width {{width}} meters.  Suppose the density of the pyramid in kg per cubic meter was \delta(x)={{densx}} at height x meters.

        {{/pyramid}}
        {{#prism}}


                Suppose a rectangular prism of height {{height}} meters had a rectangular base of width {{width}} meters and length {{length}} meters.  Suppose the density of the prism in kg per cubic meter was \delta(x)={{densx}} at height x meters.

